HEADWORD: Placoganoidei
<hw>Plac`o*ga*noi"de*i</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos>
<ety>[NL., fr. Gr. <grk>pla`x</grk>, <grk>plako`s</grk>, a tablet + NL.
<ets>ganoidei</ets>. See <er>Ganoidei</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<def>A division of ganoid fishes including those that have large
external bony plates and a cartilaginous skeleton.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

